reviews_data.review_text: When women say “I want to own a coffee shop one day,” this is exactly what is pictured-whimsy, warmth, great coffee and an added touch of the arts. I’m new to town and have tried several other cafes. They don’t even come close to this one. A wonderful place to talk to new people or friends, study, read, or just enjoy the ambiance. I love it!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow! Thank you so much! I hope we see you again, and bring your friends!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee laid back , artsy atmosphere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much! Hope to see you on your return!!

reviews_data.review_text: One of my favorite coffee shops! Been coming here for years and this family business never fails to delight me. Art lovers will feel right at home here. Plenty of fun activities and music nights throughout every month. Drinks and food are always delicious and fresh, service is wonderful, atmosphere is 10/10!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Oh my goodness! Thank you so much! We are so happy that you enjoy us that much and are looking forward to your next visit!!

reviews_data.review_text: Love love love the atmosphere here. I work on Main Street and am always excited to stop in. Staff is amazing, drinks are well crafted, and the cafe itself is clean and welcoming! Can’t say enough good things about Olive’s! Definitely check it out if you haven’t all ready!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! Looking forward to seeing you next time!!

reviews_data.review_text: Great little vibe with cool events and delicious coffee. Definitely check it out.

This locally-owned gem on Fort Mill's Main Street is a great gathering place as a cafe, ceramics studio and shop, and the site the last Saturday of every month for an amazing jazz jam session of local talent, especially area college and high school students.  We were blown away by the level of talent last night. Thought we were in a NYC jazz club.  Don't miss this place on your travels!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow!! Thank you! What a wonderful revue! We are so glad you enjoyed it! Yes Jazz night is quite magical, one of our favorite events we have. Hope to see you again real soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Great customer service and cozy place for a great coffee
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for the great review! We are looking forward to your next visit!!

reviews_data.review_text: This is the most eclectic and adorable business in Ft. Mill. My first impression walking in was joy!  There was a beautiful sculpture in the window, a piano on the right (which someone was playing for fun), vibrant art on the walls, beautiful pottery on the shelves and a smiling face behind the coffee bar. I ordered a lemonade and it was delish! However, there is a surprise behind the curtain near the coffee bar. A fully functioning pottery studio with artists creating stunning work. I was floored. I can’t believe there is so much talent in one place. The owner, Debbie, is a master potter, artist, muralist, and creates the posters for downtown events. In the evening (check schedule) there are lots of events. Jazz, open mic, music bingo, singer song writer nights all happen here as well. Go there and be amazed like I was!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow! Thank you!! What an awesome review. We are so pleased you found our place!! Looking forward to seeing you in again:)))

reviews_data.review_text: Neat little gem! The iced chai latte and muffin were excellent !
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much!! Looking forward to your next visit!!

reviews_data.review_text: My wife and I were in this area the other day and saw this on Yelp so we checked it out. The atmosphere was pretty cute and kind of has an Alice in Wonderland vibe. My wife got a dirty chai which was not amazing. The chai flavor was pretty weak, and the service was not especially friendly. Cute pottery and art if you are looking for that.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello! I’m sorry your service and product was less than perfect. I hope you will give us another try.

reviews_data.review_text:
I love Olive's! I take pottery classes here, and love the instructors and studio members. It's a very positive, encouraging atmosphere.

I'm not a coffee drinker, but I still like the cafe side of the business. They have scones and muffins and a few varieties of tea, and it's a nice place to chill, have good conversation, and see some local art. If you're there on a hot summer day, get their lemonade. Fresh squeezed and super refreshing!

If there's no on-street parking, there's more free parking behind the buildings- either turn right at Hobo's or left onto Confederate Street to find a spot.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We love having you!! People like you are who make us able to be here! Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text: Olive’s is great!  Good coffee and friendly staff!😃☕️
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Jack! We hope to see you again real soon!!

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve good experiences coming here the past few times! Drink tastes a little different every time I get it but never bad. Only issue I’ve ever really had is tables don’t seem to be clean no matter what time I come. They’re also randomly closed one morning with nothing posted in their website so I drove out just to drive 10 minutes back home. It’s a small family owned business so I understand things happen just a little disappointed
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for the constructive criticism, that’s something we all can use!
We will improve with the tables. 
One morning our Barista’s car wouldn’t start, sorry you were one who experienced that!  I’m sure there will be other times like that because, well, life happens, I’m afraid. 
However different they are, we are happy you think our drinks are good. We’ll hone that in as well. Hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Perfect spot for relaxing while you enjoy your coffee or any of the other beverages they offer. Love the art & handmade items they have available for purchase, adds a lot of charm to the place. Staff have always been very friendly and welcoming as well.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the great review!  We are looking forward to your next visit!

reviews_data.review_text: I absolutely love this place!! The coffee is always so excellent and the prices are amazing!!! When I need a good cup of coffee this is where I go! They are so nice and make you feel welcomed!!! If you are looking for a new go-to coffee shop this is the place!!! They also give amazing recommendations and I just have yet to find a better coffee shop!

reviews_data.review_text: Beware of buying clay kit deal/package for your kids. I got 2 deals for my kids, they got the clay and tools, and crafted beautiful works of art (my totally biased opinion). In Feb, I took it back to the store for them to color, glaze and bake them in the kiln to be finished. The kiln was broken and they had no idea when it would be fixed. I went back on June 21st and they couldn't find my kids stuff cuz according to them they keep them only for 60 days. I am upset that one they didn't give me a date when the kiln would be fixed,  second they didn't tell me they hold it for 60 days once finished. Finally the lady (I'm assuming is the owner) says if it is so important for you, you should have come back sooner! My kids are feeling so sad and heartbroken. What a horrible experience!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We haven’t offered these kits since 2020 and early  to mid 2021. It was a pandemic offer during close down and people who had compromised immune systems.

reviews_data.review_text:
This is a coffee shop. They also offer some pottery classes in the rear and I wasn’t always sure if it was a coffee shop. The coffee is fantastic and really good quality. I was a bit skeptical and figured it’d be average but I was pleasantly surprised. The space seemed a bit quirky the first time I walked in but I think it’s part of the artsy influence. They had a lot of pottery decor on display. I think that’s also what makes it unique - I’ve really started to like the vibe.

They have a piano and offer some classic open mic nights -which you don’t often find in a coffee shop anymore. If you’re looking for a quiet place to read a book or a spot to meet with a friend, I’d recommend checking this place out.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for giving us a try! Yes our concept is hard to list on search sites such as Google and other search engines. They make you choose only one type of service or another.
We are all about art, including the art of making coffee! Our mission is bringing the art community together and providing a great atmosphere for our guests to hang out. We hope you come back for our events and see our fun nights as well!

Is nine months long enough to wait before you decide to rave again about your favorite pit stop? I literally stop here at minimum three times a week. And if I miss a day, I come the day after. After my knee surgery I forced my husband to chauffeur me here for a London Fog. I have stopped my schoolwork to stop in this place and brought my books in, too. The little trinkets around the shop for view and for sale are so enticing to linger through while your drink is made. I love seeing what’s the next theme in the front display window. I don’t do coffee often but if you like REAL TEA LATTES, not a teabag and milk, but a real tea latte, YOU NEED TO COME IN HERE!
——————
I've been coming here for a while now for coffee, but today was a little special for me. I asked the young lady behind the counter for an earl grey tea with a side of steamed milk. I was going to make my own London Fog, because everywhere I order it, nobody has a clue what I'm talking about. She looked right at me and said "I know exactly what it is, I can make it for you." I can't explain the feeling of relief I got when she said that. I wasn't met with the rudeness and pretentiousness I get from Starbucks, the clueless looks I get from Caribou Coffee... she KNEW my drink. The tea is a beautiful aromatic blend, and the milk was steamed to perfection. I'm literally nursing my tea because I know there's a bottom to my cup! The shop is so warm and inviting. I love the small quaint feeling. I will be a regular!

My sentiments about this shop had been shared by many. It's so cute, the staff very friendly and the coffee/selection is really amazing. The kicker for me was the 3 shots in a 16oz cup! Next time we're in the area, well be sure to stop in.
Love this place!

The BEST coffee in Fort Mill! Great friendly and knowledgeable staff that make you feel like family. Perfect drinks with house made syrups that taste sooooo yummy! AND there’s great art and sometimes music! What more could you ask for? Definitely my favorite place to hang out.
Great coffee! Staff is awesome as well! Great neighbors on Main Street in Fort Mill! Sarah is da bomb!

Fantastic coffee and the shop has many interesting art pieces and such for purchase. I did not take part, but they also had an art studio there with wheels for the community to use as well as classes. I am hoping to take part in the classes in the future.

reviews_data.review_text: This is the most eclectic and adorable business in Ft. Mill. My first impression walking in was joy!  There was a beautiful sculpture in the window, a piano on the right (which someone was playing for fun), vibrant art on the walls, beautiful pottery on the shelves and a smiling face behind the coffee bar. I ordered a lemonade and it was delish! However, there is a surprise behind the curtain near the coffee bar. A fully functioning pottery studio with artists creating stunning work. I was floored. I can’t believe there is so much talent in one place. The owner, Debbie, is a master potter, artist, muralist, and creates the posters for downtown events. In the evening (check schedule) there are lots of events. Jazz, open mic, music bingo, singer song writer nights all happen here as well. Go there and be amazed like I was!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow! Thank you!! What an awesome review. We are so pleased you found our place!! Looking forward to seeing you in again:)))

reviews_data.review_text: Beware of buying clay kit deal/package for your kids. I got 2 deals for my kids, they got the clay and tools, and crafted beautiful works of art (my totally biased opinion). In Feb, I took it back to the store for them to color, glaze and bake them in the kiln to be finished. The kiln was broken and they had no idea when it would be fixed. I went back on June 21st and they couldn't find my kids stuff cuz according to them they keep them only for 60 days. I am upset that one they didn't give me a date when the kiln would be fixed,  second they didn't tell me they hold it for 60 days once finished. Finally the lady (I'm assuming is the owner) says if it is so important for you, you should have come back sooner! My kids are feeling so sad and heartbroken. What a horrible experience!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We haven’t offered these kits since 2020 and early  to mid 2021. It was a pandemic offer during close down and people who had compromised immune systems.

Is nine months long enough to wait before you decide to rave again about your favorite pit stop? I literally stop here at minimum three times a week. And if I miss a day, I come the day after. After my knee surgery I forced my husband to chauffeur me here for a London Fog. I have stopped my schoolwork to stop in this place and brought my books in, too. The little trinkets around the shop for view and for sale are so enticing to linger through while your drink is made. I love seeing what’s the next theme in the front display window. I don’t do coffee often but if you like REAL TEA LATTES, not a teabag and milk, but a real tea latte, YOU NEED TO COME IN HERE!
——————
I've been coming here for a while now for coffee, but today was a little special for me. I asked the young lady behind the counter for an earl grey tea with a side of steamed milk. I was going to make my own London Fog, because everywhere I order it, nobody has a clue what I'm talking about. She looked right at me and said "I know exactly what it is, I can make it for you." I can't explain the feeling of relief I got when she said that. I wasn't met with the rudeness and pretentiousness I get from Starbucks, the clueless looks I get from Caribou Coffee... she KNEW my drink. The tea is a beautiful aromatic blend, and the milk was steamed to perfection. I'm literally nursing my tea because I know there's a bottom to my cup! The shop is so warm and inviting. I love the small quaint feeling. I will be a regular!

My sentiments about this shop had been shared by many. It's so cute, the staff very friendly and the coffee/selection is really amazing. The kicker for me was the 3 shots in a 16oz cup! Next time we're in the area, well be sure to stop in.

Great artist-friendly space.
Love it a lot, they can make you anything and everything to do with coffee and the owners and staff are great and have awesome stories all day!
Great coffee! Cool space with a laid back atmosphere.
Great atmosphere, Very friendly service and the coffee was delicious!
